ExecDesc.value: Microsoft Office CGM Image Converter Buffer Overflow

EngDesc.value: A buffer overflow vulnerability exists in Microsoft Office. The vulnerability is due to the way Office allocates a buffer size when handling CGM image files. An attacker can leverage this vulnerability by enticing a target user to open a malicious file.Successful exploitation would allow an attacker to execute arbitrary code in the security context of the logged in user. An unsuccessful attack could cause an abnormal termination of the affected product.
